        <div class="col-xs-8 col-md-offset-2 book-container border-container-grey">
            <p>DB: What do you mean?
            <p>JK: Actuality is when there is no division between the thinker and the thought.                      
            <p>DB: But suppose I say, ordinarily one feels that the observer is different from the observed. We begin there.
            <p>JK: We begin there. I'll show you. Look at it. Are you different from your anger, from your envy, from your suffering? You are not.
            <p>DB: At first sight it appears that I am, that I might try to control it. 
            <p> JK: You are that.
            <p>DB: Yes, but how will I see that I am that?
            <p>JK: You are your name. You are your form, your body. You are the reactions and actions. You are the belief, the fear, the suffering and pleasure. You are all that.  
          </div>
        </div>        
      </div>
    </div>
