            <p>DB: But you are telling me that this unbiased observer is the same as the anger he is looking at? 
            <p>JK: Of course. Like I analyse myself and the analyser is the analysed.   
            <p> DB: Yes. He is biased by what he analyses. <p>   
            <p>JK: Of course.
            <p>DB: So if I watch anger for a while I can see that I am very biased by the anger, so at some stage I say that I am one with that anger - right?
            <p>JK: No, not I am one with it, you are it.
            <p>DB: But that anger and I are the same, right?
            <p>JK: Yes. The observer is the observed. And when there is that actuality exists you have really eliminated altogether conflict. Conflict exists when I am separate from my quality.
          </div>
